==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} ''[[puppis]]'', the "stern of a ship"
===Proper noun===
{{wikipedia|Puppis}}
'''Puppis'''

#{{constellation}}: A [[winter]] [[constellation]] of the [[northern]] sky, said to resemble the [[stern]] of a [[ship]]. Until 1763, it was part of a larger constellation, [[Argo Navis]].

